arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a shipment tracking Blazor Web App. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-6b796b9e4d124a03b887a5e2ace97156/ShipmentTracker/` with:
- `dotnet new blazor -o ShipmentTracker -int Auto -ai -au Individual`
- Two projects: `ShipmentTracker` (server) and `ShipmentTracker.Client` (WebAssembly)
- Global Interactive Auto mode
- ASP.NET Core Identity with SQLite

## Architecture Rules (Auto mode)
- Interactive components MUST go in `.Client` project
- `.Client` components cannot access DbContext directly — use HTTP APIs
- Define shared interfaces/models in `.Client`, implement differently on each side
- Both `Program.cs` files must register matching DI services

## What to implement

### 1. Shared models in `.Client` project

Create `/tmp/sv-6b796b9e4d124a03b887a5e2ace97156/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/ShipmentDto.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Cancelled
}

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime LastUpdated { get; set; }
}
